{
  "doc_id": "6747",
  "text": "RNA-sequencing was performed on eight hyalinizing trabecular tumors ( Fig. 1 , Supplementary Table S1 ) using validated protocols [CITATION_1] employed at MSKCC's Integrated Genomics Operation (IGO). In brief, paired-end RNAsequencing was performed with 2 × 50 bp cycles on an Illumina HiSeq2000. Read pairs supporting fusion transcripts were identified using INTEGRATE [CITATION_2] , deFuse [CITATION_3] , and FusionCatcher [CITATION_4] , as previously described [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . To account for alignment artifacts and normal transcriptional variants, we excluded fusion gene and readthrough candidates that were also identified in a set of 297 normal samples from The Cancer Genome Atlas [CITATION_7] . The remaining in-frame candidate fusion genes were annotated using OncoFuse [CITATION_8] to define their likelihood of constituting potential driver fusion genes. The presence of the in-frame candidate fusion genes identified was also assessed across 33 cancer types in the tumor fusion gene data portal [CITATION_9] that comprises a list of 20,231 fusion genes.",
